  "response_text": "Here's a weekly workout plan that you can follow:\n\n**Monday (Chest and Triceps):**\n\n1. Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of cardio (treadmill, bike, or elliptical)\n2. Barbell Bench Press: 3 sets of 8-12 reps\n3. Incline Dumbbell Press: 3 sets of 10-15 reps\n4. Cable Fly: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n5. Tricep Pushdown: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n6. Tricep Dips: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n7. Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching\n\n**Tuesday (Back and Biceps):**\n\n1. Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of cardio\n2. Pull-ups: 3 sets of 8-12 reps (or Assisted Pull-ups)\n3. Barbell Rows: 3 sets of 8-12 reps\n4. Lat Pulldowns: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n5. Dumbbell Bicep Curls: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n6. Hammer Curls: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n7. Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching\n\n**Wednesday (Rest Day)**\n\n**Thursday (Legs):**\n\n1. Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of cardio\n2. Squats: 3 sets of 8-12 reps\n3. Leg Press: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n4. Lunges: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (per leg)\n5. Leg Extensions: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n6. Leg Curls: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n7. Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching\n\n**Friday (Shoulders and Abs):**\n\n1. Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of cardio\n2. Shoulder Press: 3 sets of 8-12 reps\n3. Lateral Raises: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n4. Rear Delt Fly: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n5. Plank: 3 sets of 30-60 seconds\n6. Russian Twists: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n7. Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching\n\n**Saturday and Sunday (Rest Days)**\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n\n* Start with lighter weights and gradually increase the weight as you become stronger.\n* Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets, and 120-180 seconds between exercises.\n* Make sure to eat a balanced diet and stay hydrated throughout the day.\n* Get at least 7-8 hours of sleep each night to aid in muscle recovery.\n* Consult with a doctor or a certified personal trainer before starting any new workout plan.\n\nRemember, consistency and patience are key. Stick to the plan and you'll see results over time.",
